==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pavise
<hw>Pa*vise</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OF. <ets>pavaix</ets>, F. <ets>pavois</ets>; cf. It.
<ets>pavese</ets>, LL. <ets>pavense</ets>; perh. named from
<ets>Pavia</ets> in Italy.]</ety> <fld>(Mil. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A large
heavy oblong shield covering the whole body, carried by a pavisor, who
sometimes also screened an archer with it. It was originally carried but
sometimes set up in permanent position</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>pavis</asp>, <asp>pavais</asp>, <asp>pavese</asp>, and
<asp>pavesse</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pavisor</ent>⟦br⟧
